iversity of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from Gainford (Durham)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Gaynford was born in 1440, in Hampshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Sir Knight Robert White, of the Bath. She died in 1475, in her hometown, at the age of 35."},"et":{"1440–1475":"1440–1475","1438–1513":"1438–1513","1475–Male":"1475–Surnud","1513":"1513","1475":"1475","1440":"1440","about 1475":"umbes 1475","1438":"1438","South Warnborough, Hampshire, England":"South Warnborough, Hampshire, England","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1440–1475":"1440–1475","1438–1513":"1438–1513","1475–Male":"1475–Kuollut","1513":"1513","1475":"1475","1440":"1440","about 1475":"noin 1475","1438":"1438","South Warnborough, Hampshire, England":"South Warnborough, Hampshire, England","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1440–1475":"1440–1475","1438–1513":"1438–1513","1475–Male":"1475–Décédé","1513":"1513","1475":"1475","1440":"1440","about 1475":"environ 1475","1438":"1438","South Warnborough, Hampshire, England":"South Warnborough, Hampshire, Angleterre","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Margaret Gaynford est née en 1440, à Hampshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Sir Knight Robert White, of the Bath. Elle est décédée en 1475, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 35 ans."},"de":{"1440–1475":"1440–1475","1438–1513":"1438–1513","1475–Male":"1475–Verstorben","1513":"1513","1475":"1475","1440":"1440","about 1475":"um 1475","1438":"1438","South Warnborough, Hampshire, England":"South W